	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, it is true that your chances to DA are more per fight using a faster weapon than a slower weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the damage output would be the same in either case.<br><br>Yes, you will DA more often with 1HS, but the DA from the 2HS has higher damage bonus, etc.  So, if the damage output from the wepaons is equal prior to DA, then the damage output is equal after the DA.<br><br>If given option of equal damage combinations of using two 1HS versus one 2HS, I go with the dual wielding 1HS becuase then I can &quot;ghetto bash&quot; when a mob starts to cast a spell and can interrupt. (Ghetto Bash is when I drop my shield onto my secondary slot mid-fight, click BASH, then drop sword back onto Secondary slot and continue dual-wielding.)<br>&nbsp;<br>Nap0leon<br>aka Ishinru - Iksar Monk</td></tr>
